Interface ServerRequest


  • public interface ServerRequest

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void clientResponse()
      This is the action the class will perform upon the client receiving a reply from the server.
      void serverResponse()
      This is the action the server will perform upon receiving the request.

    • Method Detail

      • serverResponse

        void serverResponse()
        This is the action the server will perform upon receiving the request. It is intended that this method modify the class state so that the response contains the necessary data. However, this is not required.

      • clientResponse

        void clientResponse()
        This is the action the class will perform upon the client receiving a reply from the server. This can include updating databases, shuffling resources, or nothing at all.
